idea-plugin.change-notes:
21 Sep 2015: improvements and new inspections
<br /> 
<br /> - English language corrected (huge thanks to contributors!)
<br /> - 'strstr(...)' could be replaced with 'strpos(...)': case-insensitive invariants supported;
<br /> - Non-optimal if conditions: ambiguous instanceof checks added;
<br /> - Foreach usage possible: temporary not available due to exception introduced in PS 9.5 EAP version;
<br /> 
<br /> - 'isset(...)' usage: added reporting settings;
<br /> - 'empty(...)' usage: added reporting settings;
<br /> - 'stristr(...)/stripos()' could be replaced with 'strstr(...)/strpos()': implemented;
<br /> - Summer-time unsafe date manipulations: implemented;
<br /> 
<br />

idea-plugin.description:
EmmetEverywhere Plugin for IntelliJ IDEA
<br /> ==================================
<br /> 
<br /> WARNING!
<br /> v.1.2.3+ for JAVA 1.8
<br /> v.1.2.2 for JAVA 1.7
<br /> 
<br /> Use HTML Emmet anywhere.
<br /> For example in Google Closure Template (*.soy files).
<br /> Just type your code and press CTRL+ALT+]
<br /> 
<br /> Here’s an example: this abbreviation
<br /> 
<br /> #page&gt;div.logo+ul#navigation&gt;li*5&gt;a{Item $}
<br /> 
<br /> ...can be transformed into
<br /> 
<br /> &lt;div id=&quot;page&quot;&gt;
<br /> &lt;div class=&quot;logo&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
<br /> &lt;ul id=&quot;navigation&quot;&gt;
<br /> &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot;&gt;Item 1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
<br /> &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot;&gt;Item 2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
<br /> &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot;&gt;Item 3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
<br /> &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot;&gt;Item 4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
<br /> &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;&quot;&gt;Item 5&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
<br /> &lt;/ul&gt;
<br /> &lt;/div&gt;
<br /> 
<br /> more information about Emmet:
<br /> http://emmet.io/
<br />

SQL DAL Maker is a generator of DTO and DAO classes. Target programming languages: PHP, Java, C++, Python, Ruby.
<br /> 
<br /> To generate the class, you declare it in XML meta-program. Example:
<br /> 
<br /> &lt;dto-class name=&quot;Order&quot; ref=&quot;getOrders.sql&quot; /&gt;
<br /> 
<br /> &lt;dao-class&gt;
<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;crud-auto dto=&quot;Order&quot; table=&quot;orders&quot; /&gt;
<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;query-dto-list method=&quot;getOrders(d1, d2)&quot; ref=&quot;getOrders.sql&quot; dto=&quot;Order&quot; /&gt;
<br /> &lt;/dao-class&gt;
